values.IT_SCRIPTLINE: the engine returns the statement that will be executed next.
values.IT_MSGBOX: the engine returns a script execution error message. This type can only be returned if the parameter qInteractOnError was set to true when calling the ConfigureReload method.
values.IT_BREAK: the engine breaks and waits for a response on what to do next.
values.IT_END: the engine has finished to execute all statements in the script.

qTitle.desc:
Title used in the message box dialog. 
This property is relevant if qType is IT_MSGBOX.

qMsg.desc:
Message used in the message box dialog. 
This property is relevant if qType is IT_MSGBOX.

qButtons.desc:
Buttons displayed in the message box dialog.
 This property is relevant if qType is IT_MSGBOX.
One of:

0 means that the qButtons property is not relevant.
17 means that the message box contains the OK and Cancel buttons or the stop-sign icon.

qLine.desc:
Next script statement to be executed.
This property is used if the type of interaction is IT_SCRIPTLINE.

qOldLineNr.desc:
First line number of the previously executed statement.
This property is used if the type of interaction is IT_SCRIPTLINE.

qNewLineNr.desc:
First line number of the next statement to be executed.
This property is used if the type of interaction is IT_SCRIPTLINE.

qPath.desc:
Path specified by the Include script variable.
This property is used if the type of interaction is IT_SCRIPTLINE.
Example of an Include variable:
$(Include=lib:\\MyDataFiles\abc.txt);

qHidden.desc: This property is set to true if the returned statement is an hidden script statement.

qResult.desc: Not relevant for describing the requested user interaction.

qInput.desc: Is not used in Qlik Sense.
